Former President Olusegun Obasanjo has condemned the burning of farm in Benue State. It was gathered that about 2,420 hectares of farm at Howe in the Aliade area of Gwer East Local Government was set abaze at the weekend. Reacting to this, Obasanjo via a statement by his Special Assistant on Media, Kehinde Akinyemi said the Benue government, the LGA and security agencies have taken up the issue. JUST IN: Veteran Yoruba Actor, Tafa Oloyede Dies NECO Registrar Reveals How Borno Can Bridge Gaps In Unity… The statement said the retired General looked forward to the perpetrators’ arrest and prosecution. “The former President thanked those who had called him to identify with him on the incident”, Akinyemi added.